    comment: '<p>The <code>&#x3C;input></code> element is the most basic, and flexible form element. Interactive <code>&#x3C;input></code> elements like text fields, radio buttons, and checkboxes, must be placed within an <code>&#x3C;form></code> HTML element to collect user input.</p>\n<p>Here\'s an example of a raw text field:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;form>\n First Name:\n &#x3C;input\n  type="text"\n  name="firstname">\n  \n Last Name:\n &#x3C;input\n  type="text"\n  name="lastname">\n&#x3C;/form>\n</code></pre>\n<p><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="320" height="115"><g fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><rect width="320" height="115" fill="#FFF" rx="9"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="16"><tspan x="20" y="31">First Name</tspan></text><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="16"><tspan x="20" y="71">Last Name</tspan></text><path fill="#FFF" stroke="#CCC" d="M20.5 75.5h130v18h-130zm0-40h130v18h-130z"/></g></svg></p>\n<p>Example radio buttons: </p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;form>\n  &#x3C;input\n    type="radio"\n    name="age"\n    value="0-18"\n    checked>0-18&#x3C;br>\n  &#x3C;input\n    type="radio"\n    name="age"\n    value="19-25">19-25&#x3C;br>\n  &#x3C;input\n    type="radio"\n    name="age"\n    value="26-35">26-35&#x3C;br>\n  &#x3C;input\n    type="radio"\n    name="age"\n    value="36+">36+\n&#x3C;/form>\n</code></pre>\n<p><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="320" height="111"><g fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><rect width="320" height="111" fill="#FFF" rx="9"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="14.5"><tspan x="36" y="31">0-18</tspan></text><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="14.5"><tspan x="36" y="50">19-25</tspan></text><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="14.5"><tspan x="36" y="69">26-35</tspan></text><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="14.5"><tspan x="36" y="88">36+</tspan></text><circle cx="27" cy="27" r="7" fill="#3B99FC" stroke="#3B99FC"/><circle cx="27" cy="27" r="2.5" fill="#FFF"/><circle cx="27" cy="46" r="7" fill="#FFF" stroke="#9E9E9E"/><circle cx="27" cy="65" r="7" fill="#FFF" stroke="#9E9E9E"/><circle cx="27" cy="84" r="7" fill="#FFF" stroke="#9E9E9E"/></g></svg></p>\n<p>Example submit:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;form>\n Full name:&#x3C;br>\n &#x3C;input\n  type="text"\n  name="fullname">&#x3C;br>\n &#x3C;input\n  type="submit"\n  value="Submit">\n&#x3C;/form>\n</code></pre>\n<p><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="320" height="93"><g fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><rect width="320" height="93" fill="#FFF" rx="9"/><text fill="#000" font-family="Arial-BoldMT, Arial" font-size="11.5" font-weight="bold"><tspan x="26" y="68">Submit</tspan></text><rect width="52" height="17" x="19.5" y="55.5" stroke="#D3D3D3" rx="4"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="16"><tspan x="20" y="31">Full Name</tspan></text><path fill="#FFF" stroke="#CCC" d="M20.5 36.5h100v16h-100z"/></g></svg></p>\n<!--[View CodePen](https://codepen.io/enkidevs/pen/pZzGPJ)-->\n<p>As you can see, the <code>input</code> element is responsible for many of the form controls on the web that you are familiar with.</p>\n',
